The bamboo starts at 60 inches high. Every day it grows by 30 inches, so after $n$ days it will be at $60 + n \cdot 30 = 90 + 30n$ inches. Therefore, we have the equation $$90 + 30n = 1200.$$ Solving for $n$, we obtain
\begin{align*}
30n&=1200-90\\
n&=\frac{1110}{30}=\boxed{37}.
\end{align*}
Final Answer: The final answer is 37. I hope it is correct.

